[SN]TITLE[SN]
Met PC admits getting schoolgirl to perform sex act on Skype

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A Met police constable has admitted persuading a 14-year-old girl to perform a sex act during a Skype call.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Alistair Leiper had a series of online video chats with two teenagers between December 2013 and April 2014, Southwark Crown Court heard.
The 37-year-old pleaded guilty to three counts of attempting to engage in sexual activity in the presence of a child and one of causing or inciting a child to engage in sexual activity.
He will be sentenced on 3 March.
Judge Joanna Korner QC said she needed "to know whether he is dangerous" and ordered a pre-sentence report.
Leiper was suspended from the force when he was arrested in August 2015. He was released on bail.
